{"title":"Welcome","markdown":{"headingText":"Welcome","headingAttr":{"id":"","classes":["unnumbered"],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":true,"markdown":"\nThis book contains a presentation of Kalman filters, from basics to nonlinear and ensemble filters. \nTo understand these well, examples are provided in the form of jupyter notebooks. \nThen the notion of Bayesian inverse problems (BIP) is introduced.  Finally, there is a detailed presentation of the use of the ensemble Kalman filter as a basis for the solution of *inverse problems.* This is denoted EKI, or ensemble Kalman inversion, following the magnificent work of Andrew Stuart and his collaborators.\n\nThis book is based upon a number of sources. \nThe original Bayesian formulation for inverse problems [@Stuart2015] \nwas the basis for the later ensemble Kalman inversion, presented in a \nseries of papers [@Stuart2013; @Stuart2022; @Huang2022]. Bayesian data assimilation\nis presented in detail in [@ReichCotter2015] and a general approach to Bayesian filtering can\nbe found in [@Sarkka2023].\n\n\nIn [@Asch2016] and [@LSZ2015] the reader can find detailed \npresentations of Kalman filter approaches for data assimilation. \nIn  [@Asch2022] there are basic explanations of uncertainty \nquantification, inverse problems and their use for digital twins.\n\n## Author {.unnumbered}\n\nMark Asch is Emeritus Professor at the Universit√© de Picardie Jules Verne in the mathematics department.\n\n<https://markasch.github.io/DT-tbx-v1/>, \n\n<http://masch.perso.math.cnrs.fr/>\n\n## Citation {.unnumbered}\n\nAsch, Mark. Kalman Filters: from Bayes to Inverse Problems. Online (2024)\n<https://markasch.github.io/kfBIPq/>\n\n```tex\n@book{Asch2024\n    title = {Kalman {F}ilters: from {B}ayes to {I}nverse {P}roblems},\n\tauthor = {Asch, Mark},\n    url = {https://markasch.github.io/kfBIPq/},\n    year = {2024},\n    publisher = {Online}\n}\n```\n\n## License {.unnumbered}\n\nThis online book is frequently updated and edited. It's content is free to use, licensed under a [Creative Commons licence](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/), and the code can be found on [GitHub](https://github.com/markasch/kfbipq). A physical copy of the book will be available at a later date.\n\n**License:**  <a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/\">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International License</a>.\n\n<a rel=\"license\" href=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/\"><img alt=\"Creative Commons License\" style=\"border-width:0\" src=\"https://i.creativecommons.org/l/by-nc-sa/4.0/88x31.png\" /></a>\n\n## References  {.unnumbered}\n\n::: {#refs}\n:::\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true